cs.DM, cs.SI, cs.NA, cs.CG, cs.LG 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The paper deals with the development of a network distance metric and the identification of network invariants, which are topics that fall under discrete mathematics. 
2. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper discusses the application of the network distance metric to various subfields of topological data analysis, which includes social and information networks. 
3. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) - The paper discusses the computational complexity involved in computing the network distance metric and provides lower bounds that are easily computable, which are topics that fall under numerical analysis. 
4. cs.CG (Computational Geometry) - The paper deals with the development of a distance metric for networks, which can be viewed as a type of geometric object. 
5. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper discusses the application of the network distance metric to a database of random networks and simulated hippocampal networks, which are topics that fall under machine learning.
